    d. If x ‚â§ y and y ‚â§ z, then x ‚â§ z.
    e. x ‚â§ y or y ‚â§ x.
    f. If x ‚â§ y and y ‚â§ x, then x = y.

Proof.

    b. Suppose that x < y and y ‚â§ z.  We know that y = z or y < z.  If y = z, then x < z.  If y < z, then x < z by [transitivity of <].

    c. Suppose that x ‚â§ y and y < z.  We know that x = y or x < y.  If x = y, then y < z.  If x < y, then x < z by [transitivity of <].

